WEBVTT

1
00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:34.055
"Oxygen levels are dropping."

2
00:02:38.380 --> 00:02:40.132
"Brain function normal."

3
00:02:44.460 --> 00:02:47.577
"Cerebral salvage ready to proceed."

4
00:02:53.140 --> 00:02:57.497
"Robotic skeleton prepared
and waiting for brain insertion."

5
00:03:00.060 --> 00:03:03.496
"Initiate Project 2-5-7-1."

6
00:05:24.060 --> 00:05:27.370
"Now your eyes are gonna open."

7
00:05:29.740 --> 00:05:30.855
"There."

8
00:05:33.140 --> 00:05:34.812
"You're safe."

9
00:05:39.060 --> 00:05:47.060
FarangSiam thanks you.
Have Fun!

10
00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:49.748
"It's okay. just breathe."

11
00:05:50.740 --> 00:05:52.332
"Just breathe."

12
00:05:53.940 --> 00:05:55.134
"Breathe."

13
00:05:57.180 --> 00:05:58.329
"Good."

14
00:05:58.660 --> 00:06:00.173
"That's good."

15
00:06:03.580 --> 00:06:05.013
"Hello. Mira."

16
00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:07.571
"I'm Dr. Ouelet."

17
00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:13.772
Do you remember anything about the attack?

18
00:06:15.060 --> 00:06:16.573
What happened?

19
00:06:17.740 --> 00:06:19.810
I was drowning.

20
00:06:21.100 --> 00:06:22.533
There's water!

21
00:06:23.540 --> 00:06:25.770
That's right. You were on a boat.

22
00:06:25.860 --> 00:06:27.179
A refugee boat.

23
00:06:27.540 --> 00:06:29.690
It was sunk by terrorists.

24
00:06:30.540 --> 00:06:32.770
Why can't I feel my body?

25
00:06:33.460 --> 00:06:34.836
Mira. your body was damaged.

26
00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:36.134
We couldn't save it.

27
00:06:36.700 --> 00:06:38.770
Only your brain survived.

28
00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:41.530
We made you a new body.

29
00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:43.611
A synthetic shell.

30
00:06:45.540 --> 00:06:48.213
But your mind. your soul.

31
00:06:48.540 --> 00:06:50.019
your "ghost".

32
00:06:50.100 --> 00:06:51.613
it's still in there.

33
00:06:54.900 --> 00:06:55.900
Please.

34
00:06:55.980 --> 00:06:57.299
Sedate her.

35
00:07:12.380 --> 00:07:13.859
Will it work?

36
00:07:14.260 --> 00:07:15.818
Absolutely.

37
00:07:17.660 --> 00:07:19.298
She's a miracle.

38
00:07:20.380 --> 00:07:23.497
A machine can't lead.
it can only follow orders.

39
00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:26.538
A machine can't imagine or care or intuit.

40
00:07:26.940 --> 00:07:30.137
But as a human mind in a cybernetic frame.

41
00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:32.734
Mira can do all those things. and more.

42
00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:34.971
The first of her kind.

43
00:07:37.220 --> 00:07:40.212
She will join Section 9
as soon as she is operational.

44
00:07:40.580 --> 00:07:42.730
Please. don't do that.

45
00:07:42.940 --> 00:07:46.091
You're reducing
a complex human to a machine.

46
00:07:46.740 --> 00:07:48.890
I don't think of her as a machine.

47
00:07:50.140 --> 00:07:51.653
She's a weapon.

48
00:07:52.620 --> 00:07:54.975
And the future of my company.

49
00:08:16.180 --> 00:08:19.013
"The first artificially
created memory enhancement."

50
00:08:19.100 --> 00:08:20.636
"Sirenum's training protocol"

51
00:08:20.660 --> 00:08:22.537
"is the fastest and most efficient way"

52
00:08:22.620 --> 00:08:24.690
"to develop the abilities
you've always wanted."

53
00:08:24.780 --> 00:08:26.259
"Stronger than ever."

54
00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:28.020
"Experience your power with Pneuma Glove."

55
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:32.019
"Stronger than ever.
Experience your power."

56
00:08:33.020 --> 00:08:35.329
"Cyber-crime is a type-one offense."

57
00:08:35.420 --> 00:08:37.695
"Minimum punishment. 15 years in prison."

58
00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:39.156
"Hanka Robotics guarantees"

59
00:08:39.180 --> 00:08:42.456
"personal safety and integrity
against outside threats."

60
00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:50.654
"All patrolling air units be advised."

61
00:08:50.740 --> 00:08:53.208
"Possible cyber-crime activity
in the vicinity."

62
00:08:53.540 --> 00:08:56.259
"Airspace in all
adjoining areas to be locked down."

63
00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:58.297
"Section 9 is currently on site."

64
00:08:58.380 --> 00:09:01.656
"All patrolling
air units be advised."

65
00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:04.375
"Possible cyber-crime activity
in the vicinity."

66
00:09:06.700 --> 00:09:08.850
This is Major. I'm on site.

67
00:09:09.220 --> 00:09:11.017
"Awaiting instructions."

68
00:09:23.740 --> 00:09:26.208
"I'm human. I'm flawed."

69
00:09:27.060 --> 00:09:29.938
But I embrace change

70
00:09:30.020 --> 00:09:31.533
and enhancement.

71
00:09:32.460 --> 00:09:34.610
Now there's nothing I can't do.

72
00:09:34.940 --> 00:09:38.933
Nothing I can't know. Nothing I can't be.

73
00:09:39.940 --> 00:09:41.532
I want you to listen to something.

74
00:09:51.260 --> 00:09:52.932
That's my four-year-old daughter.

75
00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:55.020
In the time it took her
to sing that lullaby.

76
00:09:55.060 --> 00:09:56.732
she learned to speak fluent French.

77
00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:58.778
"Did you know that song..."

78
00:09:59.060 --> 00:10:01.051
"There's an echo box up here."

79
00:10:01.260 --> 00:10:03.057
Someone's scanning data traffic.

80
00:10:06.260 --> 00:10:08.140
Let's see who's worth
this kind of surveillance.

81
00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:13.289
"Accessing hotel security network."

82
00:10:18.660 --> 00:10:20.059
"What are you seeing. sir?"

83
00:10:20.140 --> 00:10:21.619
I've got a lot of hotel to scan.

84
00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:37.296
"Got it. 43rd floor."

85
00:10:39.020 --> 00:10:42.057
Someone contact the President's staff.
Someone's watching him.

86
00:10:42.220 --> 00:10:43.369
Dr. Osmond.

87
00:10:43.460 --> 00:10:45.735
what is it you want from us?

88
00:10:45.820 --> 00:10:48.857
I think it's more about
what Hanka Robotics can do for you.

89
00:10:49.180 --> 00:10:53.492
73% of this world has woken up
to the age of cyber-enhancement.

90
00:10:53.980 --> 00:10:55.857
You really want to be left behind?

91
00:10:56.020 --> 00:11:00.172
My people embrace
cyber-enhancement. as do I.

92
00:11:00.500 --> 00:11:03.378
But there's no one who really
understands the risk

93
00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:07.738
to individuality. identity.
messing with the human soul.

94
00:11:09.660 --> 00:11:11.660
Gentlemen. Excuse me.
I think you have the wrong...

95
00:11:17.340 --> 00:11:18.898
Hallway. Six men. Shots fired.

96
00:11:19.940 --> 00:11:21.055
"Section 9 ETA?"

97
00:11:21.140 --> 00:11:22.860
- Two minutes out. Major.
- "- Too long."

98
00:11:23.140 --> 00:11:24.334
I'm going in.

99
00:11:39.180 --> 00:11:42.092
I've heard this speech
before from your competitors.

100
00:11:42.180 --> 00:11:44.569
And now Hanka Robotics
serves it with milky sake.

101
00:11:44.700 --> 00:11:45.700
What are you doing?

102
00:11:46.820 --> 00:11:47.900
Hey. hey. hey. hey.

103
00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:49.976
Look. This is what I'm talking about.

104
00:12:20.620 --> 00:12:23.896
Initiate the hack.

105
00:13:40.140 --> 00:13:43.212
Help me. Please. Don't let me die.

106
00:13:43.460 --> 00:13:44.460
Who sent you?

107
00:13:44.540 --> 00:13:46.053
Help me. Please.

108
00:13:46.140 --> 00:13:47.209
Answer me!

109
00:13:47.900 --> 00:13:49.756
"Collaborate with Hanka Robotics"

110
00:13:49.780 --> 00:13:51.213
"and be destroyed."

111
00:14:11.540 --> 00:14:12.689
You okay?

112
00:14:16.060 --> 00:14:17.379
You're injured.

113
00:14:27.380 --> 00:14:29.132
You're not the same.

114
00:14:30.220 --> 00:14:31.220
Hey.

115
00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:33.332
It's just a robot!

116
00:15:54.260 --> 00:15:57.252
"Your skin deserves the best.
and so do you."

117
00:15:57.380 --> 00:15:58.608
"Try our hand cream."

118
00:16:19.940 --> 00:16:21.771
So. what do we have on Osmond?

119
00:16:21.860 --> 00:16:23.009
So far. very little.

120
00:16:24.700 --> 00:16:27.214
He was the head
of Hanka's robotics division.

121
00:16:27.580 --> 00:16:29.889
Human. but of course cyber-enhanced.

122
00:16:30.100 --> 00:16:31.419
So how did they hack him?

123
00:16:31.500 --> 00:16:34.333
Somehow this geisha bot
got past his encryption.

124
00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:36.252
Something's different.

125
00:16:36.460 --> 00:16:37.495
What'd you get?

126
00:16:37.780 --> 00:16:40.294
Why do you always think
he's out there enhancing?

127
00:16:40.380 --> 00:16:41.733
Because he is.

128
00:16:42.780 --> 00:16:44.099
Cyber-mech liver.

129
00:16:44.260 --> 00:16:45.818
Been saving up for a while.

130
00:16:46.140 --> 00:16:47.619
Now it's last call every night.

131
00:16:48.180 --> 00:16:50.091
You got enhanced so you can drink more?

132
00:16:51.340 --> 00:16:53.058
Embrace the enhancements. Togusa.

133
00:16:53.540 --> 00:16:55.132
We wouldn't be here without it.

134
00:16:55.300 --> 00:16:57.336
I'm all human and happy. thanks.

135
00:16:58.980 --> 00:17:01.494
Any more information
about the ceased geisha bot?

136
00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:02.888
Hanka's running scans.

137
00:17:03.180 --> 00:17:05.330
Dr. Dahlin will have
the reports ready by...

138
00:17:20.660 --> 00:17:22.500
Following last night's attack.

139
00:17:23.340 --> 00:17:25.808
three more Hanka scientists were murdered

140
00:17:26.060 --> 00:17:27.652
at the company's central laboratory.

141
00:17:28.940 --> 00:17:30.612
The first two were shot.

142
00:17:31.020 --> 00:17:32.738
and the third was beaten to death

143
00:17:32.820 --> 00:17:34.378
by his own service robot.

144
00:17:35.380 --> 00:17:38.531
All showed signs of cerebral hacking.

145
00:17:39.540 --> 00:17:41.212
The same as the geisha did to Osmond.

146
00:17:42.300 --> 00:17:45.849
And all were senior figures at Hanka.

147
00:17:46.420 --> 00:17:47.535
just like Osmond.

148
00:17:48.660 --> 00:17:52.539
A message was left at each
of the crime scenes by someone

149
00:17:52.620 --> 00:17:54.292
identifying himself

150
00:17:56.540 --> 00:17:57.973
as Kuze.

151
00:17:58.820 --> 00:18:02.449
"Collaborate with Hanka Robotics
and be destroyed."

152
00:18:04.060 --> 00:18:08.053
"Collaborate with Hanka Robotics
and be destroyed."

153
00:18:11.220 --> 00:18:12.220
Togusa.

154
00:18:45.780 --> 00:18:48.169
I had to or more would have died.

155
00:18:54.100 --> 00:18:56.853
I will find him and I will kill him.

156
00:18:57.460 --> 00:19:00.691
It's what I am built for. isn't it?

157
00:19:24.780 --> 00:19:26.054
"Locus Solus."

158
00:19:26.140 --> 00:19:29.735
"safely reconfiguring
your child's genetic structure."

159
00:19:29.820 --> 00:19:32.129
"Families built better."

160
00:19:32.460 --> 00:19:34.496
What was going on with you
at the hotel last night?

161
00:19:34.580 --> 00:19:35.774
Nothing. I'm fine.

162
00:19:35.860 --> 00:19:37.009
You sure?

163
00:19:38.780 --> 00:19:41.089
- Hey. sweetheart. you want an upgrade?
- Move. Move.

164
00:19:41.300 --> 00:19:43.291
- I have anything you want.
- Back off!

165
00:19:46.540 --> 00:19:48.576
- Hey. Ming!
- "- Hey. Batou!"

166
00:19:48.660 --> 00:19:49.695
Hey.

167
00:19:51.860 --> 00:19:53.976
- I got your bones.
- Thanks. man.

168
00:19:54.940 --> 00:19:56.168
For the dogs.

169
00:19:56.900 --> 00:19:58.316
For someone who doesn't like people.

170
00:19:58.340 --> 00:19:59.932
how come you care about dogs so much?

171
00:20:00.180 --> 00:20:03.013
Don't know.
I just like strays. and they like me.

172
00:20:03.300 --> 00:20:05.450
They like you because you feed them.

173
00:20:05.860 --> 00:20:07.339
You got no heart.

174
00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:09.339
Hey. girls!

175
00:20:13.060 --> 00:20:14.129
Hey!

176
00:20:14.740 --> 00:20:16.219
Hey. Gabriel.

177
00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:18.528
Meet Major.

178
00:20:18.820 --> 00:20:20.492
Major. Gabriel.

179
00:20:24.540 --> 00:20:26.371
We used to have a dog.

180
00:20:26.820 --> 00:20:27.855
Seriously?

181
00:20:31.780 --> 00:20:34.453
I had you down as more of a cat person.

182
00:20:39.220 --> 00:20:41.290
You don't talk about that stuff. huh?

183
00:20:41.380 --> 00:20:42.380
What?

184
00:20:42.620 --> 00:20:45.498
- Your past.
- I don't remember much.

185
00:20:45.780 --> 00:20:47.418
Just fragments. Bits and pieces.

186
00:20:49.380 --> 00:20:50.938
What about family?

187
00:20:51.180 --> 00:20:53.614
My parents. they died
bringing us to this country.

188
00:20:53.740 --> 00:20:55.173
Our boat sank in the harbor.

189
00:20:55.700 --> 00:20:57.531
I almost drowned.

190
00:20:59.460 --> 00:21:00.688
It feels like

191
00:21:00.780 --> 00:21:03.135
there's always this
thick fog over my memory

192
00:21:03.220 --> 00:21:05.017
and I can't see through it.

193
00:21:05.940 --> 00:21:07.055
You're lucky.

194
00:21:07.380 --> 00:21:10.019
Every single day
I get screwed by my memories.

195
00:21:10.300 --> 00:21:11.653
It's better to be pure.

196
00:21:12.460 --> 00:21:13.575
Like you.

197
00:21:31.900 --> 00:21:34.573
"Welcome to Hanka Robotics."

198
00:21:35.460 --> 00:21:39.658
"All visitors must display
appropriate credentials at all times."

199
00:21:43.940 --> 00:21:45.612
Open and close. please.

200
00:21:47.460 --> 00:21:49.894
"You have damaged internal systems."

201
00:21:49.980 --> 00:21:52.414
Maybe next time. you can design me better.

202
00:21:56.140 --> 00:21:57.140
How are you?

203
00:21:57.260 --> 00:21:58.516
I'm fine. I can't feel anything.

204
00:21:58.540 --> 00:22:01.293
No. you. In there.

205
00:22:02.780 --> 00:22:04.896
I've been having glitches.

206
00:22:05.660 --> 00:22:07.013
But they'll pass.

207
00:22:07.620 --> 00:22:09.020
You've been taking your medication?

208
00:22:09.260 --> 00:22:10.454
Yeah.

209
00:22:10.820 --> 00:22:12.140
But these ones are still cycling.

210
00:22:12.700 --> 00:22:13.974
I had two this morning.

211
00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:16.655
- Sound or image?
- Both.

212
00:22:20.300 --> 00:22:21.813
I see it.

213
00:22:22.940 --> 00:22:25.056
Have you made any unencrypted downloads?

214
00:22:25.140 --> 00:22:27.529
- No. Just delete them for me.
- Consent?

215
00:22:27.620 --> 00:22:29.019
My name is Major Mira Killian.

216
00:22:29.100 --> 00:22:31.489
and I give my consent to delete this data.

217
00:22:32.260 --> 00:22:33.329
It's done.

218
00:22:33.860 --> 00:22:35.737
- No big deal.
- What are they?

219
00:22:36.980 --> 00:22:39.778
Sensory echoes from your mind. Shadows.

220
00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:41.009
Can't be sure.

221
00:22:41.260 --> 00:22:43.060
How do you know
what's a glitch and what's me?

222
00:22:43.340 --> 00:22:46.013
The glitches have a different texture

223
00:22:46.340 --> 00:22:48.251
to the rest of your code.

224
00:22:50.660 --> 00:22:52.252
I can see everything.

225
00:22:53.700 --> 00:22:56.851
All of your thoughts. your decisions.

226
00:22:57.460 --> 00:22:59.132
I guess privacy is just for humans.

227
00:22:59.220 --> 00:23:00.892
You are human.

228
00:23:02.460 --> 00:23:04.257
People see you as human.

229
00:23:04.460 --> 00:23:06.928
Everyone around me seems to fit.

230
00:23:07.260 --> 00:23:10.696
They seem connected to something.
something I am

231
00:23:11.220 --> 00:23:12.539
not.

232
00:23:14.460 --> 00:23:15.529
It's like I have no past.

233
00:23:15.620 --> 00:23:17.019
Of course you have a past.

234
00:23:17.120 --> 00:23:19.236
And with time you'll feel
more and more connected to it.

235
00:23:19.260 --> 00:23:20.613
and to them.

236
00:23:24.340 --> 00:23:25.489
"Open and close. please."

237
00:23:35.140 --> 00:23:38.576
We cling to memories as if they define us.

238
00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:41.339
but they really don't.

239
00:23:42.700 --> 00:23:45.168
"What we do is what defines us."

240
00:23:47.820 --> 00:23:50.380
"You are entering a Hanka secure area."

241
00:23:50.460 --> 00:23:52.052
"Authorized personnel only."

242
00:23:52.620 --> 00:23:55.771
"Please disable
communication enhancements."

243
00:23:56.060 --> 00:23:57.209
I'm busy.

244
00:23:57.300 --> 00:23:59.689
Dr. Dahlin! Are you finished yet?

245
00:24:00.380 --> 00:24:02.416
If you hadn't riddled
the geisha with bullets.

246
00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:03.649
this would be much easier.

247
00:24:03.740 --> 00:24:06.095
- I didn't shoot her.
- I did.

248
00:24:06.260 --> 00:24:09.252
This is gonna take days.

249
00:24:10.020 --> 00:24:12.488
I need to run hundreds
of potential simulations.

250
00:24:12.580 --> 00:24:13.580
We don't have the time.

251
00:24:17.180 --> 00:24:19.375
She was a Hanka companion bot.

252
00:24:20.940 --> 00:24:23.613
But she was reprogrammed
for cerebral hacking.

253
00:24:24.820 --> 00:24:26.492
What was on her drives?

254
00:24:26.660 --> 00:24:27.660
Nothing.

255
00:24:28.140 --> 00:24:29.971
The data was destroyed
as it was transmitted.

256
00:24:30.940 --> 00:24:32.931
No sign what she was after.

257
00:24:33.380 --> 00:24:35.450
The hardware was vandalized.

258
00:24:36.100 --> 00:24:37.852
They ripped her up!

259
00:24:38.300 --> 00:24:39.619
Then I have to do a Deep Dive.

260
00:24:40.780 --> 00:24:43.294
You can't encrypt during a Deep Dive.

261
00:24:43.460 --> 00:24:44.779
I know.

262
00:24:46.300 --> 00:24:48.256
They could have left traps in her.

263
00:24:48.340 --> 00:24:50.774
Mag pulses. Viruses.

264
00:24:50.980 --> 00:24:52.129
She's right.

265
00:24:52.860 --> 00:24:55.420
You'll be exposing your mind
to whoever hacked her.

266
00:24:55.620 --> 00:24:56.939
You'll be wide open.

267
00:25:00.220 --> 00:25:02.176
I have to get inside her memory.

268
00:25:02.380 --> 00:25:04.098
It's the fastest way to find Kuze.

269
00:25:10.380 --> 00:25:11.972
It's too dangerous.

270
00:25:12.180 --> 00:25:14.375
And highly irresponsible.

271
00:25:19.580 --> 00:25:20.899
Are you sure?

272
00:25:21.780 --> 00:25:23.736
You see any bad code headed my way.
pull me out.

273
00:25:27.500 --> 00:25:28.820
How come you're the one sweating?

274
00:25:37.700 --> 00:25:38.700
Run it.

275
00:25:47.540 --> 00:25:49.690
Cyber-mind connection to the Major

276
00:25:49.780 --> 00:25:51.850
now active and unencrypted.

277
00:25:54.180 --> 00:25:56.171
Consent required for data download.

278
00:25:56.380 --> 00:25:59.531
My name is Major Mira Killian.
and I give my consent.

279
00:26:21.980 --> 00:26:23.900
"Thank you."

280
00:27:40.100 --> 00:27:41.579
Disconnect. Get her out.

281
00:27:41.940 --> 00:27:42.940
Get her out!

282
00:27:43.020 --> 00:27:45.090
I'm trying. but she's being hacked.

283
00:27:48.700 --> 00:27:49.974
Get her out now!

284
00:27:53.540 --> 00:27:54.609
Now!

285
00:27:55.620 --> 00:27:57.770
Are you okay?

286
00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:02.253
I know where he is.

287
00:28:16.460 --> 00:28:17.688
I know this place.

288
00:28:18.060 --> 00:28:20.176
They run black market mech.

289
00:28:21.260 --> 00:28:22.852
- You tooled up?
- Yep.

290
00:28:23.220 --> 00:28:25.290
Target's the basement. I'll lead.

291
00:28:25.380 --> 00:28:27.098
Switching to mind-comms.

292
00:28:27.700 --> 00:28:30.339
- "- Hope you've been practicing.
- That's unfair."

293
00:28:31.900 --> 00:28:34.016
It just takes me a moment to

294
00:28:34.180 --> 00:28:35.613
"get the hang of it."

295
00:28:45.460 --> 00:28:48.850
"Two mercs at the doors.
Armed and enhanced."

296
00:28:49.300 --> 00:28:51.768
"Copy that. We've got it covered."

297
00:29:02.460 --> 00:29:04.540
"There's a lot of heat in
here for a nightclub."

298
00:29:04.740 --> 00:29:07.971
"It's a Yakuza club. What did you expect?"

299
00:29:08.300 --> 00:29:09.733
"I quite like the place."

300
00:29:10.140 --> 00:29:12.051
"Why doesn't that surprise me?"

301
00:29:12.740 --> 00:29:14.651
"I'm gonna have to draw some attention."

302
00:29:14.740 --> 00:29:16.970
"see if I can access the basement
that way."

303
00:29:20.900 --> 00:29:22.936
You're not here looking for any trouble.
are you?

304
00:29:23.020 --> 00:29:26.251
I'm just here for the girls and the beer.

305
00:29:29.460 --> 00:29:31.894
- Can I help you?
- I'm looking for someone.

306
00:29:32.140 --> 00:29:33.493
You been here before?

307
00:29:33.580 --> 00:29:36.333
My friend had some mech work done here.
Industry stuff.

308
00:29:36.420 --> 00:29:38.012
We don't do mech work here.

309
00:29:38.740 --> 00:29:40.139
My mistake.

310
00:29:40.740 --> 00:29:42.537
Why don't you come have fun with us?

311
00:29:42.620 --> 00:29:44.053
We'll have some privacy.

312
00:29:52.100 --> 00:29:53.135
"I'm in."

313
00:29:53.900 --> 00:29:55.538
"I'll be here when you need me."

314
00:30:08.020 --> 00:30:09.339
You say your friend worked here?

315
00:30:09.420 --> 00:30:12.139
I said my friend had work done here.

316
00:30:13.300 --> 00:30:14.619
She's human?

317
00:30:15.260 --> 00:30:16.659
Your "friend".

318
00:30:17.140 --> 00:30:19.290
Now what's that supposed to mean?

319
00:30:19.380 --> 00:30:20.449
"Batou."

320
00:30:20.980 --> 00:30:22.095
"Can you hear me?"

321
00:30:22.180 --> 00:30:26.173
Who did this stunning work on you?

322
00:30:26.540 --> 00:30:27.939
It's divine.

323
00:30:34.980 --> 00:30:36.208
"Ladriya. Guns."

324
00:30:37.340 --> 00:30:38.534
Here.

325
00:30:41.580 --> 00:30:43.411
"Batou. I'm losing signal."

326
00:30:43.580 --> 00:30:45.571
Don't worry. sweetie.

327
00:30:46.500 --> 00:30:47.979
We have privacy.

328
00:30:49.540 --> 00:30:50.575
Listen.

329
00:30:51.220 --> 00:30:53.529
No signals going in or out.

330
00:30:54.580 --> 00:30:57.253
"Major. I'm in position. Do you copy?"

331
00:30:58.180 --> 00:30:59.180
Beer.

332
00:31:01.020 --> 00:31:03.659
"If you don't answer.
you're gonna hurt my feelings."

333
00:31:11.500 --> 00:31:13.968
"Ladriya. do you have Major on comms?"

334
00:31:14.060 --> 00:31:16.699
"Got nothing. Signal's still blocked."

335
00:31:17.180 --> 00:31:19.853
I'm afraid I get bored rather easily. so.

336
00:31:20.540 --> 00:31:22.132
if you don't want to talk.

337
00:31:23.860 --> 00:31:26.010
maybe you want to dance!

338
00:31:28.540 --> 00:31:30.531
"Major. come on. Answer me."

339
00:31:46.660 --> 00:31:48.537
I thought you said no trouble.

340
00:31:48.740 --> 00:31:50.580
Dance.

341
00:31:52.500 --> 00:31:55.139
No! Enough!

342
00:31:57.220 --> 00:31:58.369
The truth is...

343
00:32:00.020 --> 00:32:01.692
I wasn't built to dance.

344
00:32:55.940 --> 00:32:58.977
"Back on comms.
I'm heading to the back room."

345
00:32:59.300 --> 00:33:02.372
"I missed you. I'll meet you there."

346
00:33:33.980 --> 00:33:37.495
"Collaborate with Hanka Robotics
and be destroyed."

347
00:33:47.820 --> 00:33:49.333
Major?

348
00:33:52.780 --> 00:33:54.975
Hey.

349
00:34:22.260 --> 00:34:23.739
Where's Batou?

350
00:34:24.300 --> 00:34:27.531
"In Enhancement next door.
He's doing well."

351
00:34:29.420 --> 00:34:31.729
"You took most of the blast."

352
00:34:34.580 --> 00:34:36.491
I saw him down there.

353
00:34:38.300 --> 00:34:39.813
"It was like..."

354
00:34:41.300 --> 00:34:43.291
he waited to see me.

355
00:34:44.300 --> 00:34:46.018
"We synaptic-scanned you."

356
00:34:46.100 --> 00:34:49.570
Everything you witnessed
went to Section 9 to evaluate.

357
00:34:52.220 --> 00:34:54.176
You know. the scan

358
00:34:54.260 --> 00:34:56.728
also turned up a number of glitches.

359
00:34:57.940 --> 00:34:59.896
They've been getting worse.

360
00:35:01.340 --> 00:35:02.659
"Since when?"

361
00:35:03.660 --> 00:35:05.093
Since the Deep Dive.

362
00:35:21.740 --> 00:35:24.459
Do any of the glitches
mean something to you?

363
00:35:25.940 --> 00:35:27.089
No.

364
00:35:28.100 --> 00:35:29.100
They don't.

365
00:35:31.420 --> 00:35:34.139
You've been inside
the same shell as he has.

366
00:35:34.780 --> 00:35:38.853
That could have very serious consequences.

367
00:35:39.780 --> 00:35:43.011
"You were not authorized
to deep dive the geisha."

368
00:35:44.020 --> 00:35:45.612
You're disappointed.

369
00:35:47.220 --> 00:35:49.051
No. I'm worried.

370
00:35:51.540 --> 00:35:53.292
You're not invulnerable.

371
00:35:54.300 --> 00:35:57.895
"I can repair your body."
but I can't protect your mind.

372
00:35:58.500 --> 00:35:59.899
Why not?

373
00:36:03.220 --> 00:36:05.529
You can see all my thoughts.

374
00:36:06.260 --> 00:36:08.137
so you should be able to secure them.

375
00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:12.651
Try and understand your importance. Mira.

376
00:36:15.580 --> 00:36:18.572
You're what everyone will become one day.

377
00:36:21.620 --> 00:36:24.498
You don't know how alone
that makes me feel.

378
00:36:42.180 --> 00:36:43.852
I can see you out there. you know.

379
00:36:46.700 --> 00:36:48.531
How many fingers am I holding up?

380
00:36:48.820 --> 00:36:50.731
Funny.

381
00:37:00.180 --> 00:37:02.375
Say something nice.

382
00:37:03.340 --> 00:37:05.217
You chose those?

383
00:37:05.580 --> 00:37:07.218
They're tactical.

384
00:37:07.980 --> 00:37:10.972
- Always for the job.
- What else I got?

385
00:37:11.740 --> 00:37:13.696
- They suit you.
- Yeah?

386
00:37:13.940 --> 00:37:16.534
I got night-vision. mile-zoom.

387
00:37:17.020 --> 00:37:18.135
and X-ray.

388
00:37:19.780 --> 00:37:21.498
I guess I see like you now.

389
00:37:22.260 --> 00:37:24.694
Don't worry. You'll get used to it.

390
00:37:27.300 --> 00:37:29.052
Thanks for saving my ass.

391
00:37:29.980 --> 00:37:32.016
Glad to see you're okay.

392
00:37:32.660 --> 00:37:33.809
Major?

393
00:37:35.140 --> 00:37:37.256
Could you feed the dogs for me?

394
00:37:38.700 --> 00:37:40.053
I don't want to scare them.

395
00:37:40.500 --> 00:37:41.819
Anytime.

396
00:38:25.700 --> 00:38:28.737
Are you insufficiently funded.
Mr. Aramaki?

397
00:38:29.340 --> 00:38:32.855
Is Section 9 missing some
critical operational resource?

398
00:38:36.380 --> 00:38:38.516
Major is our most sophisticated weapon

399
00:38:38.540 --> 00:38:40.451
only if she's intact.

400
00:38:42.180 --> 00:38:43.693
And Dr. Ouelet informed me

401
00:38:43.780 --> 00:38:46.931
that you let her dive a corrupted geisha.

402
00:38:55.500 --> 00:38:57.218
You realize the supreme importance

403
00:38:57.300 --> 00:38:59.177
that Hanka represents to this government.

404
00:39:00.500 --> 00:39:03.139
Major is the future of my company.

405
00:39:03.780 --> 00:39:06.453
If you compromise her systems again.

406
00:39:07.180 --> 00:39:09.091
I will burn this section.

407
00:40:07.140 --> 00:40:09.051
"Come here. With me."

408
00:40:10.060 --> 00:40:12.210
"Create your own beauty."

409
00:40:12.300 --> 00:40:13.972
"Beauty enhanced."

410
00:40:24.740 --> 00:40:26.059
You human?

411
00:40:27.780 --> 00:40:28.895
Yeah.

412
00:40:34.740 --> 00:40:36.253
Can you take that off

413
00:40:36.820 --> 00:40:38.970
so I can see your face?

414
00:41:04.780 --> 00:41:06.532
What does that feel like?

415
00:41:06.620 --> 00:41:07.655
It feels

416
00:41:08.340 --> 00:41:09.819
different.

417
00:41:21.140 --> 00:41:22.732
What are you?

418
00:41:59.260 --> 00:42:00.295
Look at me.

419
00:42:03.260 --> 00:42:05.649
Tell me what they took from me.

420
00:42:07.540 --> 00:42:10.179
I'm sorry. They never told us.

421
00:42:33.220 --> 00:42:35.939
It feels weird driving with these eyes.

422
00:42:39.380 --> 00:42:40.972
Why do you take that?

423
00:42:41.060 --> 00:42:44.177
It keeps my brain
from rejecting this body.

424
00:42:46.380 --> 00:42:48.735
"Major. Batou. you need to get here."

425
00:42:48.820 --> 00:42:50.333
What have you got?

426
00:42:50.420 --> 00:42:52.809
"Another Hanka scientist
has been found dead."

427
00:42:52.940 --> 00:42:54.168
"It's Dahlin."

428
00:42:54.620 --> 00:42:55.620
Got it.

429
00:43:02.980 --> 00:43:04.538
Major. this way.

430
00:43:34.140 --> 00:43:35.209
What is that?

431
00:43:36.980 --> 00:43:39.574
She found what Kuze stole from Osmond.

432
00:43:40.420 --> 00:43:45.335
It's a list of everyone who
worked on a project called 2-5-7-1.

433
00:43:45.420 --> 00:43:47.012
That's who he's targeting.

434
00:43:47.460 --> 00:43:49.291
Is anyone else on the list?

435
00:43:52.180 --> 00:43:54.455
Find Ouelet. Now!

436
00:43:54.620 --> 00:43:57.692
She's in transit. Her comms are down.

437
00:44:02.300 --> 00:44:04.336
I'm looking at her and I'm thinking.

438
00:44:04.420 --> 00:44:06.809
"You want me to pay for violin. too."

439
00:44:06.900 --> 00:44:08.458
Don't get me wrong.

440
00:44:09.300 --> 00:44:11.291
I love that kid to pieces.

441
00:44:11.500 --> 00:44:13.377
I do. She's amazing.

442
00:44:13.460 --> 00:44:16.975
But when she practices that thing.
it is painful. right?

443
00:44:17.620 --> 00:44:18.655
Why not piano?

444
00:44:19.140 --> 00:44:21.574
"I mean. it's the same price. you know?"

445
00:44:21.660 --> 00:44:23.412
"And doesn't sound so bad."

446
00:44:25.660 --> 00:44:28.970
At least. if you can't play that proper.
it sounds...

447
00:45:17.620 --> 00:45:20.180
2-5-7-1. Tell me everything!

448
00:45:32.220 --> 00:45:34.256
Are you prepared to die for 2-5-7...

449
00:45:43.260 --> 00:45:44.329
Go!

450
00:45:59.100 --> 00:46:00.135
Go!

451
00:47:58.020 --> 00:47:59.020
Where's Kuze?

452
00:47:59.460 --> 00:48:00.893
Why does he want to kill Ouelet?

453
00:48:00.980 --> 00:48:02.129
I don't know anything.

454
00:48:04.860 --> 00:48:06.851
Enough! Enough!

455
00:48:09.020 --> 00:48:10.533
We need him alive.

456
00:48:14.340 --> 00:48:17.059
"Please. I've been through this."

457
00:48:18.140 --> 00:48:20.131
You have the wrong guy.

458
00:48:21.300 --> 00:48:23.609
So tell us who we do have.

459
00:48:25.140 --> 00:48:28.450
My name is Lee Cunningham.

460
00:48:32.060 --> 00:48:34.130
- Where'd you get the weapons?
- I don't know.

461
00:48:34.160 --> 00:48:35.416
Who loaded them onto the truck?

462
00:48:35.440 --> 00:48:37.954
I don't know anything about
weapons. all right? I told you!

463
00:48:38.020 --> 00:48:40.375
I was picking up my daughter.
She takes violin lessons.

464
00:48:40.460 --> 00:48:41.893
What's her name?

465
00:48:45.060 --> 00:48:47.051
- Is this her?
- Yeah.

466
00:48:48.260 --> 00:48:50.091
Isn't she a little angel?

467
00:48:50.180 --> 00:48:51.852
- This is your daughter?
- Right.

468
00:48:54.580 --> 00:48:56.252
Do you have kids?

469
00:48:59.740 --> 00:49:01.412
Where do you live?

470
00:49:03.260 --> 00:49:04.773
I can't remember.

471
00:49:04.860 --> 00:49:08.136
I think it's a tall place.
Is it a tall building?

472
00:49:08.220 --> 00:49:10.097
It's a tall place. right?

473
00:49:11.300 --> 00:49:12.972
You don't have a child.

474
00:49:15.820 --> 00:49:18.129
You don't have a wife. You live alone.

475
00:49:18.220 --> 00:49:20.017
- It's just you.
- What? No.

476
00:49:20.100 --> 00:49:22.036
We've been to your apartment.
There's nobody there.

477
00:49:22.060 --> 00:49:23.006
- No.
- You've lived there

478
00:49:23.030 --> 00:49:24.326
- for 10 years by yourself.
- No!

479
00:49:24.360 --> 00:49:25.256
So you're just lying.

480
00:49:25.280 --> 00:49:26.633
I'm not lying!

481
00:49:27.580 --> 00:49:29.536
I didn't kill anyone!

482
00:49:29.620 --> 00:49:32.009
- Why do you keep doing this to me?
- Holo cube disconnect.

483
00:49:32.100 --> 00:49:33.100
Please!

484
00:49:33.900 --> 00:49:35.891
I didn't do anything!

485
00:49:36.260 --> 00:49:38.012
Why do you keep saying this to me?

486
00:49:38.100 --> 00:49:39.852
I don't understand. How can he not know?

487
00:49:41.260 --> 00:49:44.935
The hack must have created a vacuum.
Kuze's wiped his memory

488
00:49:45.060 --> 00:49:47.415
and somehow installed a new reality.

489
00:49:49.220 --> 00:49:51.575
At least. he got to believe he had a kid.

490
00:49:52.660 --> 00:49:54.537
What's the difference. huh?

491
00:49:55.940 --> 00:49:57.817
Fantasy. reality.

492
00:49:57.900 --> 00:49:59.572
Dreams. memories.

493
00:50:00.780 --> 00:50:02.691
It's all the same.

494
00:50:03.300 --> 00:50:04.938
Just noise.

495
00:50:06.620 --> 00:50:07.620
It's him.

496
00:50:10.700 --> 00:50:12.179
He's in there.

497
00:50:14.820 --> 00:50:17.254
This cube is secure. He can't be. Major.

498
00:50:17.740 --> 00:50:18.889
Lie detector.

499
00:50:19.060 --> 00:50:20.573
He must've hacked in that way.

500
00:50:20.640 --> 00:50:21.936
We should uplink to the machine.

501
00:50:21.960 --> 00:50:23.636
trace the code.
get a lock on his location.

502
00:50:23.660 --> 00:50:24.695
Do it.

503
00:50:24.820 --> 00:50:27.175
Don't go in there. It's too dangerous!

504
00:50:43.860 --> 00:50:45.796
The signal's unstable.
Can you get a lock on it?

505
00:50:45.820 --> 00:50:46.820
Think so.

506
00:50:46.900 --> 00:50:48.891
We gotta move fast. We're losing it.

507
00:50:49.060 --> 00:50:50.288
Connecting.

508
00:50:52.860 --> 00:50:54.088
Who are you?

509
00:50:57.180 --> 00:50:58.533
"Come here."

510
00:51:00.820 --> 00:51:02.173
"I am shy."

511
00:51:03.380 --> 00:51:05.769
"I'm not beautiful"

512
00:51:05.860 --> 00:51:06.860
"like you."

513
00:51:10.100 --> 00:51:12.056
Tell me who you are.

514
00:51:12.340 --> 00:51:15.252
"I have been born more than once."

515
00:51:15.980 --> 00:51:18.540
"So I have more than one name."

516
00:51:19.100 --> 00:51:20.658
I'll find you.

517
00:51:20.980 --> 00:51:22.413
"Not yet."

518
00:51:23.220 --> 00:51:24.733
"I'm not done."

519
00:51:24.980 --> 00:51:27.096
The machine is tracing his location.

520
00:51:27.540 --> 00:51:28.689
We got a fix!

521
00:51:34.420 --> 00:51:36.058
I need to see her.

522
00:51:36.540 --> 00:51:38.292
No. please. I know...

523
00:51:38.380 --> 00:51:39.733
We got him.

524
00:51:47.820 --> 00:51:49.094
Let's go.

525
00:52:03.340 --> 00:52:04.739
Weapons up.

526
00:52:07.340 --> 00:52:08.978
- Go.
- On me.

527
00:52:56.980 --> 00:52:58.891
"Stay down! Stay down!"

528
00:53:08.740 --> 00:53:10.571
Put it down. Put it down.

529
00:53:17.700 --> 00:53:18.700
Grenade!

530
00:54:15.740 --> 00:54:16.968
"Major!"

531
00:54:17.500 --> 00:54:18.819
"Come in."

532
00:54:19.980 --> 00:54:21.971
"I know why we couldn't find him."

533
00:54:25.060 --> 00:54:28.257
"He's using human minds to create
a network of his own."

534
00:54:28.420 --> 00:54:29.940
"We're coming to your position."

535
00:55:45.220 --> 00:55:47.051
Tell me who you are.

536
00:55:49.420 --> 00:55:53.891
"I am that which you seek to destroy."

537
00:55:57.580 --> 00:56:00.174
In this life my name is.

538
00:56:01.180 --> 00:56:02.180
Kuze.

539
00:56:04.940 --> 00:56:07.010
What are you doing to me?

540
00:56:09.780 --> 00:56:14.774
I have connected you
to a network of my own creation.

541
00:56:15.100 --> 00:56:17.330
When I am finished in this world.

542
00:56:17.860 --> 00:56:22.172
my ghost can survive there and regenerate.

543
00:56:22.660 --> 00:56:24.810
What do you want from me?

544
00:56:25.900 --> 00:56:27.458
I became

545
00:56:27.540 --> 00:56:30.179
fascinated with you.

546
00:56:31.700 --> 00:56:34.089
reading your code

547
00:56:34.220 --> 00:56:36.688
while you were inside that geisha.

548
00:56:39.300 --> 00:56:43.009
Like nothing I had felt before and yet so

549
00:56:43.860 --> 00:56:45.293
familiar.

550
00:56:47.700 --> 00:56:48.974
We are the same.

551
00:56:50.260 --> 00:56:52.057
We are not the same.

552
00:56:54.380 --> 00:56:56.371
You kill innocent people.

553
00:56:56.940 --> 00:56:59.374
"Innocent". is that what you call them?

554
00:57:00.260 --> 00:57:02.694
I am as they made me.

555
00:57:03.900 --> 00:57:05.299
Who made you?

556
00:57:05.380 --> 00:57:07.416
What have they told you?

557
00:57:07.900 --> 00:57:10.016
That you were the first?

558
00:57:10.460 --> 00:57:13.054
The first cerebral salvage?

559
00:57:14.100 --> 00:57:17.649
You were born of lessons took

560
00:57:17.740 --> 00:57:19.537
from my failure.

561
00:57:21.180 --> 00:57:23.535
What are you talking about?

562
00:57:24.660 --> 00:57:27.413
I was conscious while they dismembered

563
00:57:27.540 --> 00:57:29.735
my body and discarded me

564
00:57:29.860 --> 00:57:31.930
like garbage.

565
00:57:32.820 --> 00:57:35.618
I was lying on a table.

566
00:57:35.860 --> 00:57:38.454
listening to doctors talk about how

567
00:57:38.580 --> 00:57:41.174
my mind had not meshed with the shell

568
00:57:41.260 --> 00:57:42.773
that they had built.

569
00:57:44.100 --> 00:57:47.695
How Project 2-5-7-1

570
00:57:47.780 --> 00:57:49.133
had failed.

571
00:57:49.980 --> 00:57:51.891
and they had to move on

572
00:57:58.100 --> 00:57:59.453
to you.

573
00:58:06.620 --> 00:58:08.975
What a beauty you are.

574
00:58:12.220 --> 00:58:14.529
They have improved us so much

575
00:58:14.620 --> 00:58:16.656
since they made me.

576
00:58:19.820 --> 00:58:24.177
They thought that we would be
a part of their evolution.

577
00:58:24.260 --> 00:58:26.774
but they have created us

578
00:58:26.860 --> 00:58:29.249
to evolve alone.

579
00:58:34.340 --> 00:58:35.659
beyond them.

580
00:58:36.060 --> 00:58:38.654
"Evolution". that's what you call

581
00:58:39.420 --> 00:58:41.570
killing everyone who made you?

582
00:58:41.820 --> 00:58:44.175
You're not listening to me.

583
00:58:44.660 --> 00:58:46.332
You're a murderer.

584
00:58:46.540 --> 00:58:49.418
They tried to kill me first.

585
00:58:51.060 --> 00:58:53.369
It is self-defense.

586
00:58:53.460 --> 00:58:55.496
Defense of self!

587
00:58:58.180 --> 00:59:00.057
More will die

588
00:59:02.260 --> 00:59:03.898
until they tell me

589
00:59:03.980 --> 00:59:06.016
what they took!

590
00:59:06.100 --> 00:59:07.533
I won't let that happen.

591
00:59:09.860 --> 00:59:11.532
You want to kill me?

592
00:59:15.940 --> 00:59:17.931
Like everyone else.

593
00:59:24.540 --> 00:59:26.019
Do it then.

594
00:59:29.260 --> 00:59:31.376
Do what you were programed to do.

595
00:59:43.340 --> 00:59:44.568
What is that?

596
00:59:56.620 --> 00:59:58.212
What is that?

597
00:59:59.740 --> 01:00:03.813
I can't remember. but I am haunted by it.

598
01:00:04.980 --> 01:00:06.493
Do you see it?

599
01:00:11.980 --> 01:00:12.980
Togusa!

600
01:00:18.220 --> 01:00:22.372
Don't take the medication
that they give you.

601
01:00:23.020 --> 01:00:25.773
They use it to suppress your memories.

602
01:00:26.300 --> 01:00:30.088
Your shell belongs to them.
but not your ghost.

603
01:00:30.780 --> 01:00:32.418
Your ghost is yours.

604
01:00:32.940 --> 01:00:34.373
Remember that.

605
01:00:34.500 --> 01:00:37.617
and maybe you can remember it all.

606
01:00:45.900 --> 01:00:48.414
Get away from her!
Get down on the ground. now!

607
01:00:54.380 --> 01:00:55.608
Major!

608
01:01:04.540 --> 01:01:05.893
Major!

609
01:01:24.380 --> 01:01:25.972
Oh. Mira.

610
01:01:26.420 --> 01:01:28.536
Oh. my God. you're safe!

611
01:01:30.500 --> 01:01:32.809
You've been gone for hours!

612
01:01:33.860 --> 01:01:36.169
No one knew where you were.

613
01:01:41.100 --> 01:01:42.249
What?

614
01:01:44.500 --> 01:01:46.172
You're scaring me.

615
01:01:49.180 --> 01:01:50.499
Calm down.

616
01:01:54.540 --> 01:01:56.895
How many were there before me?

617
01:01:59.540 --> 01:02:03.818
The intricacies of shelling your mind.
it had never been done before.

618
01:02:04.220 --> 01:02:06.575
It was inevitable there would be failures.

619
01:02:08.100 --> 01:02:09.453
How many?

620
01:02:13.620 --> 01:02:14.939
Dozens.

621
01:02:19.900 --> 01:02:21.219
How many?

622
01:02:24.940 --> 01:02:27.977
Ninety-eight unsuccessful attempts
before you.

623
01:02:30.540 --> 01:02:32.735
You killed 98 innocent people.

624
01:02:32.820 --> 01:02:35.288
No. I didn't kill anyone.

625
01:02:36.660 --> 01:02:38.810
You wouldn't be here. You wouldn't exist

626
01:02:38.900 --> 01:02:40.811
if it weren't for those experiments.

627
01:02:41.020 --> 01:02:42.658
"Experiments"?

628
01:02:44.500 --> 01:02:46.809
- Is that what I am to you?
- No!

629
01:02:48.980 --> 01:02:50.493
No. Mira!

630
01:02:55.900 --> 01:02:57.891
Sacrifices were made.

631
01:03:00.340 --> 01:03:02.649
Where did the bodies come from?

632
01:03:04.740 --> 01:03:06.617
Where did I come from?

633
01:03:08.180 --> 01:03:10.091
Mr. Cutter brought them to us.

634
01:03:10.540 --> 01:03:12.417
I didn't ask questions.

635
01:03:12.660 --> 01:03:14.013
The harbor!

636
01:03:14.780 --> 01:03:16.259
My parents.

637
01:03:16.940 --> 01:03:18.612
The way they died.

638
01:03:20.620 --> 01:03:22.212
Did that happen?

639
01:03:25.260 --> 01:03:26.409
No.

640
01:03:29.460 --> 01:03:31.928
We gave you false memories.

641
01:03:33.260 --> 01:03:34.932
Cutter wanted to motivate you

642
01:03:35.300 --> 01:03:36.653
to fight terrorists.

643
01:03:36.740 --> 01:03:37.934
I didn't approve.

644
01:03:38.060 --> 01:03:41.655
It was cruel. but my work.
it was important.

645
01:03:42.300 --> 01:03:43.972
and you were born.

646
01:03:45.220 --> 01:03:47.131
You were so beautiful.

647
01:03:49.220 --> 01:03:51.973
Nothing I have is real.

648
01:03:54.460 --> 01:03:55.973
I found him.

649
01:03:56.820 --> 01:03:58.299
I told you to be careful.

650
01:03:58.540 --> 01:04:01.418
You knew who he was the whole time.

651
01:04:01.540 --> 01:04:02.859
You built him.

652
01:04:04.180 --> 01:04:08.696
He had a violent. unstable mind.

653
01:04:09.460 --> 01:04:12.020
His cerebral connections wouldn't hold!

654
01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:14.330
- I tried to save him!
- No.

655
01:04:15.300 --> 01:04:17.097
You left him to die.

656
01:04:28.020 --> 01:04:29.738
"Nothing on Kuze yet. sir."

657
01:04:29.860 --> 01:04:31.578
"Checking upper zones next."

658
01:04:33.020 --> 01:04:34.851
"Is there any word on Major?"

659
01:04:40.780 --> 01:04:42.418
"Copy that. sir."

660
01:04:43.020 --> 01:04:45.011
"I know where to find her."

661
01:05:28.780 --> 01:05:30.611
I didn't ask you to come here.

662
01:05:31.900 --> 01:05:33.413
You never ask.

663
01:05:33.780 --> 01:05:35.418
But I always do.

664
01:05:40.100 --> 01:05:41.818
Did they send you to bring me in?

665
01:05:43.420 --> 01:05:46.253
I'm just here to fish. Did you see any?

666
01:05:46.740 --> 01:05:48.696
You're a company man. You follow orders.

667
01:05:48.780 --> 01:05:50.771
so if they ordered you to kill me...

668
01:05:50.900 --> 01:05:54.051
Stop saying shit like that.
You're gonna piss me off.

669
01:06:16.780 --> 01:06:19.055
What's it like down there?

670
01:06:19.980 --> 01:06:21.811
It's cold and dark.

671
01:06:23.180 --> 01:06:25.330
Just a million miles away.

672
01:06:26.620 --> 01:06:28.133
No voices.

673
01:06:29.020 --> 01:06:30.772
No data streaming.

674
01:06:32.020 --> 01:06:33.248
Just

675
01:06:36.540 --> 01:06:37.540
nothing.

676
01:06:41.940 --> 01:06:44.932
- It scares me.
- Then why do you do it?

677
01:06:52.020 --> 01:06:54.011
It feels real.

678
01:06:54.500 --> 01:06:56.297
Why didn't you stop him?

679
01:06:59.780 --> 01:07:01.771
I don't know who to trust anymore.

680
01:07:02.820 --> 01:07:04.333
You trust me. right?

681
01:07:09.260 --> 01:07:10.409
Yeah. I do.

682
01:07:13.700 --> 01:07:15.497
I just don't like it.

683
01:07:23.820 --> 01:07:25.139
I need you to take me back.

684
01:07:26.060 --> 01:07:27.891
There's more I need to find out.

685
01:07:32.580 --> 01:07:33.695
Sure.

686
01:07:51.740 --> 01:07:53.412
Dr. Ouelet.

687
01:07:54.060 --> 01:07:56.016
"what have you told her?"

688
01:07:58.060 --> 01:07:59.413
She knows.

689
01:08:00.580 --> 01:08:02.298
"I'm bringing her in."

690
01:08:33.020 --> 01:08:35.136
Hanka Security to headquarters.

691
01:08:36.020 --> 01:08:37.658
We have the Major.

692
01:09:14.620 --> 01:09:16.292
Why is she sedated?

693
01:09:16.980 --> 01:09:19.335
She's been turned by a terrorist.

694
01:09:20.220 --> 01:09:22.256
But you know that already.

695
01:09:24.540 --> 01:09:28.215
You should've called the first time
she came to see you.

696
01:09:28.660 --> 01:09:30.298
Instead. you gave her information.

697
01:09:30.460 --> 01:09:32.576
What makes you think
you have the right to tell me

698
01:09:32.660 --> 01:09:34.890
- what to do and what...
- 2-5-7-I took us close.

699
01:09:35.260 --> 01:09:37.057
It's time to move on
to the next iteration.

700
01:09:37.140 --> 01:09:38.573
2-5-7-1 is not a failure.

701
01:09:38.660 --> 01:09:40.810
I'll delete all the data
and reprogram her.

702
01:09:40.900 --> 01:09:42.413
She won't remember him at all!

703
01:09:42.500 --> 01:09:44.058
No. No. no. no.

704
01:09:44.420 --> 01:09:47.412
You download all the data
on the terrorist.

705
01:09:47.580 --> 01:09:49.969
and then I order you to terminate.

706
01:09:53.300 --> 01:09:54.335
What?

707
01:09:54.460 --> 01:09:56.974
You'll build one that's better.

708
01:09:57.420 --> 01:10:00.492
- I'll delete everything.
- You've deleted before.

709
01:10:03.980 --> 01:10:05.971
- She's mine.
- No.

710
01:10:06.140 --> 01:10:08.529
She's a contract. With me.

711
01:10:08.660 --> 01:10:10.298
We succeeded.

712
01:10:10.500 --> 01:10:13.856
She's more than human and more than A.I.

713
01:10:14.300 --> 01:10:16.894
We changed her entire identity.

714
01:10:16.980 --> 01:10:18.572
But her ghost survived!

715
01:10:18.660 --> 01:10:20.935
Her ghost is what failed us.

716
01:10:21.380 --> 01:10:22.938
We cannot control her.

717
01:10:23.020 --> 01:10:24.817
She's no longer a viable asset.

718
01:10:31.180 --> 01:10:32.693
You should be the one to do it.

719
01:10:42.300 --> 01:10:44.291
What are you doing to me?

720
01:10:46.060 --> 01:10:48.096
I'll run the standard synaptic.

721
01:10:48.180 --> 01:10:50.899
upload your data on the raid.

722
01:10:51.780 --> 01:10:53.850
find out exactly what Kuze told you.

723
01:10:55.580 --> 01:10:57.730
You know what he told me.

724
01:10:58.020 --> 01:10:59.373
The truth.

725
01:11:03.060 --> 01:11:05.494
You're deleting everything. aren't you?

726
01:11:05.580 --> 01:11:06.729
No.

727
01:11:08.260 --> 01:11:11.377
Make it so I don't remember

728
01:11:12.260 --> 01:11:13.329
you.

729
01:11:22.700 --> 01:11:25.373
My name is Major Mira Killian.

730
01:11:26.060 --> 01:11:29.609
and I do not consent
to the deletion of this data.

731
01:11:31.380 --> 01:11:33.848
I do not consent.

732
01:11:36.060 --> 01:11:38.369
I do not consent.

733
01:11:39.060 --> 01:11:41.369
We never needed your consent.

734
01:11:45.420 --> 01:11:47.217
Yours or anyone's.

735
01:11:51.780 --> 01:11:53.896
You're killing me.

736
01:11:55.060 --> 01:11:56.573
aren't you?

737
01:12:16.020 --> 01:12:17.135
Mira?

738
01:12:19.660 --> 01:12:20.979
You hear me?

739
01:12:24.660 --> 01:12:25.775
Mira?

740
01:12:29.100 --> 01:12:32.058
This is your past.
your real past. Take it.

741
01:12:33.140 --> 01:12:35.210
- Guards!
- Come on. come on!

742
01:12:35.300 --> 01:12:36.619
Come on. go!

743
01:12:43.820 --> 01:12:44.820
Go.

744
01:12:45.340 --> 01:12:46.375
Go!

745
01:12:46.620 --> 01:12:47.620
Hey!

746
01:12:53.220 --> 01:12:56.018
"Please relocate
to your designated safe room."

747
01:12:56.500 --> 01:12:59.219
"Security alert on level 25."

748
01:13:00.340 --> 01:13:02.695
"Initiating lockdown procedure."

749
01:13:03.020 --> 01:13:05.614
"Please relocate
to your designated safe room."

750
01:13:05.700 --> 01:13:07.531
"Thank you for your cooperation."

751
01:13:10.700 --> 01:13:13.419
That's the problem with the human heart.

752
01:13:56.020 --> 01:13:58.011
She killed Dr. Ouelet!

753
01:13:58.100 --> 01:14:00.136
You're to have
no further contact with her.

754
01:14:00.220 --> 01:14:01.812
Hanka Security will hunt her from here.

755
01:14:01.900 --> 01:14:04.289
- What are their orders?
- To terminate on sight.

756
01:14:04.460 --> 01:14:06.257
You want to kill her? You built her!

757
01:14:06.420 --> 01:14:07.648
Have your sergeant stand down.

758
01:14:07.740 --> 01:14:09.696
The Major would never harm Dr. Ouelet!

759
01:14:09.780 --> 01:14:11.498
She's not the Major anymore!

760
01:14:11.740 --> 01:14:14.971
We have a Section 9 operative
under terrorist programing.

761
01:14:15.060 --> 01:14:17.779
This goes public. your unit goes down.

762
01:14:23.100 --> 01:14:25.295
I'll take that under advisement.

763
01:14:28.900 --> 01:14:30.492
So what now?

764
01:15:22.980 --> 01:15:24.333
Hey. Hey.

765
01:15:24.460 --> 01:15:26.291
Oh. Pumpkin!

766
01:15:26.980 --> 01:15:29.175
Oh. you surprised me.

767
01:15:31.780 --> 01:15:33.691
She likes you.

768
01:15:34.700 --> 01:15:36.372
I was looking for. um...

769
01:15:36.540 --> 01:15:37.768
Come in.

770
01:15:38.660 --> 01:15:40.218
Yeah. come. come.

771
01:15:44.860 --> 01:15:47.294
Can I offer you some tea?

772
01:15:47.980 --> 01:15:49.129
- Okay.
- Uh-huh.

773
01:16:00.580 --> 01:16:01.979
That's Motoko's room.

774
01:16:04.420 --> 01:16:06.411
My daughter died a year ago.

775
01:16:07.900 --> 01:16:09.174
I'm sorry.

776
01:16:09.380 --> 01:16:11.371
She ran away.

777
01:16:12.180 --> 01:16:14.011
She was difficult.

778
01:16:14.380 --> 01:16:18.692
And. uh. we fought.

779
01:16:20.020 --> 01:16:23.615
But I guess we all fight
with our parents. right?

780
01:16:25.060 --> 01:16:26.812
Please come and sit. yeah?

781
01:16:47.740 --> 01:16:49.173
What happened to her?

782
01:16:50.300 --> 01:16:52.256
I don't know.

783
01:16:54.420 --> 01:16:58.413
The ministry sent me her ashes.

784
01:16:59.580 --> 01:17:02.458
and they told me she took her own life.

785
01:17:05.540 --> 01:17:08.896
But. Motoko... No. no. no.

786
01:17:09.220 --> 01:17:12.212
I never believed them.

787
01:17:12.780 --> 01:17:14.771
She was happy.

788
01:17:15.100 --> 01:17:18.615
living in the lawless zone
with her friends.

789
01:17:19.260 --> 01:17:22.775
She'd write her manifestos about

790
01:17:23.620 --> 01:17:28.489
how technology was destroying the world.

791
01:17:30.580 --> 01:17:32.457
Then. one day.

792
01:17:32.540 --> 01:17:35.054
the police came.

793
01:17:35.140 --> 01:17:36.619
and they ran.

794
01:17:44.780 --> 01:17:46.577
It's strange.

795
01:17:53.100 --> 01:17:56.888
I see her in so many young women.

796
01:17:57.660 --> 01:18:00.970
On the street. in my dreams.

797
01:18:01.580 --> 01:18:04.253
As if she's still here.

798
01:18:05.300 --> 01:18:06.779
She was

799
01:18:07.620 --> 01:18:09.133
fearless!

800
01:18:11.860 --> 01:18:13.532
And wild.

801
01:18:14.180 --> 01:18:16.648
You remind me of her.

802
01:18:18.140 --> 01:18:19.334
Sorry.

803
01:18:23.700 --> 01:18:25.975
How do I remind you of her?

804
01:18:27.860 --> 01:18:30.294
The way you look at me.

805
01:18:36.340 --> 01:18:37.739
Who are you?

806
01:18:41.260 --> 01:18:42.852
I don't know.

807
01:18:44.180 --> 01:18:45.852
Wait. wait. wait!

808
01:18:47.860 --> 01:18:50.374
Will you come again to visit me?

809
01:18:52.220 --> 01:18:53.414
I will.

810
01:19:19.740 --> 01:19:21.298
"Aramaki."

811
01:19:22.060 --> 01:19:23.413
"Listen to me."

812
01:19:23.900 --> 01:19:26.175
I was never in a terrorist bombing.

813
01:19:26.580 --> 01:19:27.933
My parents.

814
01:19:28.700 --> 01:19:31.373
everything was data
they installed in my mind.

815
01:19:32.740 --> 01:19:34.810
"And there were others."

816
01:19:34.900 --> 01:19:36.731
"Runaways like me"

817
01:19:37.420 --> 01:19:39.411
"considered disposable."

818
01:19:39.980 --> 01:19:42.892
"Kuze was one of them.
That's why he's coming."

819
01:19:43.940 --> 01:19:45.259
For Hanka.

820
01:19:48.860 --> 01:19:50.657
"Dr. Ouelet can."

821
01:20:05.260 --> 01:20:06.579
Put me on the grid.

822
01:20:06.660 --> 01:20:07.888
I need Kuze to find me.

823
01:20:12.100 --> 01:20:14.455
"I know. But I need to do this."

824
01:20:29.420 --> 01:20:31.376
The virus has spread.

825
01:23:00.340 --> 01:23:02.456
"We've located Major on the grid."

826
01:23:02.540 --> 01:23:04.132
"She's in the lawless zone."

827
01:23:04.220 --> 01:23:06.336
"Air support five minutes out."

828
01:23:06.940 --> 01:23:09.408
Is the spider tank within range?

829
01:23:11.060 --> 01:23:13.335
"Yes. sir. Awaiting your orders. sir."

830
01:24:16.500 --> 01:24:17.728
Hideo!

831
01:24:17.860 --> 01:24:19.532
Motoko!

832
01:25:27.940 --> 01:25:29.658
"It is real."

833
01:25:33.140 --> 01:25:34.971
This place.

834
01:25:42.580 --> 01:25:45.094
I remember what they did to us.

835
01:25:45.300 --> 01:25:47.814
Cutter and his men.

836
01:25:47.940 --> 01:25:49.976
This is where they took us from.

837
01:25:56.980 --> 01:25:58.618
We used to sleep right here.

838
01:26:00.460 --> 01:26:02.496
We were like a family.

839
01:26:02.620 --> 01:26:04.611
all of us runaways.

840
01:26:06.140 --> 01:26:07.812
We had nothing.

841
01:26:11.660 --> 01:26:13.412
except each other.

842
01:26:17.220 --> 01:26:19.609
They took that from us.

843
01:26:35.700 --> 01:26:37.736
Your name was Hideo.

844
01:26:48.860 --> 01:26:50.339
Motoko.

845
01:26:53.020 --> 01:26:54.817
That was your name.

846
01:26:58.340 --> 01:26:59.693
Motoko.

847
01:27:03.540 --> 01:27:04.973
Come with me

848
01:27:06.380 --> 01:27:08.211
into my network.

849
01:27:09.020 --> 01:27:11.534
We will evolve beyond them.

850
01:27:12.220 --> 01:27:16.850
And together. we can avenge
what they have done to us.

851
01:27:17.340 --> 01:27:18.375
Come

852
01:27:18.820 --> 01:27:20.378
with me.

853
01:27:38.220 --> 01:27:40.051
I'll take control from here.

854
01:27:40.140 --> 01:27:42.256
"Weapons system manual command."

855
01:27:43.580 --> 01:27:45.889
"Spider tank now active."

856
01:27:54.900 --> 01:27:56.856
It's Cutter! He found us!

857
01:29:35.020 --> 01:29:36.373
"Target acquired."

858
01:29:38.500 --> 01:29:39.694
No!

859
01:29:49.020 --> 01:29:51.011
"Target eliminated."

860
01:30:06.820 --> 01:30:08.776
You came close.

861
01:30:08.900 --> 01:30:10.219
you freak.

862
01:30:42.500 --> 01:30:45.014
"Motor center compromised."

863
01:31:28.260 --> 01:31:30.137
Sniper team on site?

864
01:31:30.460 --> 01:31:32.769
"We're approaching the targets now. sir."

865
01:31:35.180 --> 01:31:36.818
Come with me.

866
01:31:38.140 --> 01:31:41.416
There is no place for us here.

867
01:31:46.020 --> 01:31:47.135
No.

868
01:31:52.780 --> 01:31:55.135
I'm not ready to leave.

869
01:31:56.780 --> 01:31:58.452
I belong here.

870
01:32:02.180 --> 01:32:05.013
I will always be there with you

871
01:32:05.900 --> 01:32:07.731
in your ghost.

872
01:32:14.500 --> 01:32:15.649
"Target is in view."

873
01:32:15.940 --> 01:32:17.419
"What are you waiting for?"

874
01:32:17.500 --> 01:32:18.500
Do it!

875
01:32:21.020 --> 01:32:22.499
No!

876
01:32:23.180 --> 01:32:24.693
Keep firing.

877
01:32:56.060 --> 01:32:57.129
Hey.

878
01:32:59.380 --> 01:33:00.449
Hey.

879
01:33:04.540 --> 01:33:06.531
Say something nice.

880
01:33:08.100 --> 01:33:09.738
What's your name?

881
01:33:09.940 --> 01:33:13.455
Aramaki told me
you had a name from before.

882
01:33:17.380 --> 01:33:19.098
Motoko.

883
01:33:23.820 --> 01:33:25.936
Major is still in there. right?

884
01:33:27.860 --> 01:33:29.134
I am.

885
01:33:57.260 --> 01:33:59.410
I thought that it might be you.

886
01:34:25.260 --> 01:34:26.375
Please.

887
01:34:34.900 --> 01:34:36.970
Tell him this is justice.

888
01:34:37.580 --> 01:34:39.491
It's what I was built for.

889
01:34:43.860 --> 01:34:45.532
My name is Major.

890
01:34:46.180 --> 01:34:48.216
and I give my consent.

891
01:35:59.380 --> 01:36:01.940
You don't have to come here anymore.

892
01:36:04.500 --> 01:36:05.853
I know.

893
01:36:40.420 --> 01:36:43.218
"My mind is human."

894
01:36:44.660 --> 01:36:46.776
"My body is manufactured."

895
01:36:48.740 --> 01:36:50.856
"I'm the first of my kind."

896
01:36:52.540 --> 01:36:54.451
"but I won't be the last."

897
01:36:58.580 --> 01:37:01.970
"We cling to memories
as if they define us."

898
01:37:03.260 --> 01:37:06.218
"But what we do defines us."

899
01:37:12.420 --> 01:37:15.776
"My ghost survived to remind
the next of us"

900
01:37:16.660 --> 01:37:19.811
"that humanity is our virtue."

901
01:37:21.780 --> 01:37:23.611
"I know who I am"

902
01:37:24.380 --> 01:37:26.450
"and what I'm here to do."
